# Display_QC Project - PostgreSQL Setup and SQLAlchemy Connection

This README provides step-by-step instructions to set up the `preset` PostgreSQL database, import CSV data into the `placements` table, and connect using SQLAlchemy in Python.  

---

## 1. Install PostgreSQL (Ubuntu / WSL)

```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install postgresql postgresql-client
psql --version

# Create role for Linux user
sudo -u postgres createuser -s user_til

# Create database named "preset" owned by user_til
sudo -u postgres createdb preset -O user_til
```

```bash
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS placements;

CREATE TABLE placements (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    website TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (website <> ''),
    platform TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (platform <> ''),
    section TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (section <> ''),
    geo TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (geo <> ''),
    placement TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (placement <> ''),
    ad_unit_type TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (ad_unit_type <> ''),
    ad_sizes TEXT,  -- can be NULL
    supported_innovations TEXT,  -- can be NULL
    placement_name TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (placement_name <> '')
);
```
```bash
\copy placements(website,platform,section,geo,placement,ad_unit_type,ad_sizes,supported_innovations,placement_name)
FROM '/path/to/csv' CSV HEADER;
```